public interface Builder<T>

A basic interface describing the builder design pattern used within the library.

Method Detail

build

void build()
           throws ChemicalException
This function must build the product of the builder design pattern. This function may throw a ChemicalException if the builder needs more parameters before processing to the effective building. These parameters depend on the product built, and the builder implementation class have to provide the director a setter for each parameter.

Throws:
ChemicalException

getProduct

T getProduct()
             throws ChemicalException
Returns the built product. Throws a ChemicalException if the product isn't built yet. A prior call to build() is necessary.

Returns:
The built product.
Throws:
ChemicalException
